# Garlic Pasta

If you are short on food or broke then this recipe might be for you.

- ‚è≤Ô∏è Prep time: 3 min
- üç≥ Cook time: 10 min
- üçΩÔ∏è Servings: Depends

## Ingredients

- Pasta
- Butter or any oil-based spread
- Garlic
- Pepper
- Dried parmesan (Optional)
- Basil (Optional)

## Directions

1. Get out a large pot then fill it up with water.
2. Bring the pot to a boil, Once boiling add the pasta. Bring the pot to a simmer.
3. When the pasta achieves a "al dante" texture, strain the pasta then add it back to the pot.
4. Add butter, garlic and pepper (Adjust to you liking)
5. If you are using basil, then finely chop the herb. and mix in the pasta
6. When your pasta is thoroughly mixed, serve well. Best with parmesan sprinkled on top

